incident_updates.body: Our providers continuing to work on a fix for this issue.
The issue has been identified and a fix is being implemented.

Start time : 02/09/2024 10:30 UTC Service impact : API calls to metrics endpoints are erroring. Database service functionality is not impacted and should continue to work as expected. Ongoing actions : Investigating Our providers are working on the issue. Update will be posted as significant progress is made.

As part of our continuous improvement plan, maintenance is scheduled on our network infrastructure. This may temporarily affect Latency. Start time : 16/09/2024 20:00 UTC End time : 17/09/2024 04:00 UTC Service impact : None. Except in rare case latencies may be noted to reach PCI instances running Service improvement : Following our continuous improvement policy of our products and services, we will carry out a network hardware upgrade in our Graveline Datacenters The operation is carried out in several steps: - Step 1: Preparation of the operation (about 3 hours) - Step 2: New hardware implementation (about 2 hours) - Step 3: Test and activation of the new hardware (about 2 hours) The critical phase of this upgrade is tentatively scheduled between 10:30 PM UTC and 12:00 AM UTC. We are not expecting any impact. However in case of an issue the rollback can be managed in less than 30 minutes.
